Step 1 -Firstly setup and install magento243 on your local Environment

Step 2 - Install node and yarn on your system



****Now Steps for setup Pwa with magento2 *****

Step 3 - Go to html directory and run command (yarn create @magento/pwa)

Step 4 - After that follow the instructions shown in terminal

Step 5 - go to pwa diretory by command (cd pwa)

Step 6 - run command   (yarn run buildpack create-custom-origin ./	)

Step 7 - run command   (yarn run watch)

    ******** After running this command you will show some error, so follow these instructions to resolve these issue****

Step 8 -  Go to magento2 setup root dierctory 

Step 9  - run command (git clone https://github.com/magento/magento2-pwa.git /home/admin/public_html//vendor/ext/magento/magento2-pwa)

step 10 - run command (composer config minimum-stability dev)

step 11 - run command (composer config repositories.ext path "./vendor/ext///*")

step 12 - run command (composer require magento/pwa)

step 13 - run command (php bin/magento module:enable --clear-static-content Magento_ContactGraphQlPwa)

step 14 - run command (php bin/magento module:enable --clear-static-content Magento_NewsletterGraphQlPwa)

step 15 - Come back to PWA directory and execute (yarn run watch)

step 16 - run command (yarn run storybook)

step 16 - run command (yarn run build)

step 16 - run command (yarn start)



/usr/local/php81/bin/php bin/magento module:enable --clear-static-content Magento_NewsletterGraphQlPwa


